refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
callablenullset_exception_handler callablenullcallback
Pushes a user function (callback) onto the exception handler stack to handle uncaught exceptions. Each call to set_exception_handler pushes a new handler onto the stack, and restore_exception_handler pops the most recent one off. Execution will stop after the callback is called.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the previously defined exception handler, or &null; on error. If
 no previous handler was defined, &null; is also returned.

  &reftitle.examples;



    set_exception_handler example


<?php
function exception_handler(Throwable $exception) {
  echo "Uncaught exception: " , $exception->getMessage(), "\n";
}

set_exception_handler('exception_handler');

throw new Exception('Uncaught Exception');
echo "Not Executed\n";
?>
